  <p>Sanatan Dharma, often referred to as Hinduism in the modern world, is not just a religion but the eternal way of life. The word <span class="highlight">“Sanatan”</span> means eternal, timeless, and indestructible. Unlike other faiths that originated at a certain point in history, Sanatan Dharma has no founder and no beginning. It is rooted in the cosmic truths revealed in the Vedas and carried forward through countless sages, saints, kings, and ordinary devotees. In this section, we will explore in depth how Sanatan Dharma evolved, what it teaches, who protected it, and why it remains as relevant today as it was thousands of years ago.</p>

  <h2>1. The Timeless Origins</h2>
